parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Brake Pad Wear and ABS Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of brake pads and malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to slide or vibrate when braking, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out excessively
requiring frequent replacements; ABS brakes lock up
causing the vehicle to slide or vibrate; vehicle moves side to side or lurches forward when applying brakes; brake pedal pulsates or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Brake Caliper and Control Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper and control module can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake caliper and control module failure; ABS system malfunction; premature brake pad wear; vehicle vibration or sliding when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injection pump can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's RPMs rev to 1500 or above
the vehicle acts as if it's missing
the vehicle cuts off at times
the vehicle shuts off while driving at any speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden engine stalling and loss of power can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts down or cuts off completely while driving
loss of steering ability
loss of braking ability
near-collision or collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Electronic Throttle Control System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control system can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts down or cuts off completely while driving
loss of power
difficulty accelerating
hesitation or stumbling when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Diagnosis and Repair by Dealership
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability of the dealership to diagnose and repair the problem can lead to continued safety risks, as the vehicle remains in an unsafe condition.
symptoms: The dealership is unable to diagnose the problem
the dealership is unable to repair the problem
the vehicle remains in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause vibrations, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates excessively
especially when driving at high speeds
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle wobbles or shakes
the rear of the vehicle sagging or leaning
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shock absorbers can cause vibrations, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates excessively
especially when driving at high speeds
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle wobbles or shakes
the rear of the vehicle sagging or leaning
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
clutch line blows
roll pin backs out of slave cylinder.
